sentences: Choi Moon-ju (born August 4, 1985), better known as Choi Soo-eun is a South Korean actress and singer.
Soo-eun debuted as a member of the girl group Gangkiz in 2012, their group released mini album "We Became Gang" and repackaged mini album "Mama" in the same year.
A year later, she left the group and became an actress.
